(2075, 329, 8, 'Cut the rolled dough into 25 2\" squares.'),
(2076, 329, 9, 'Place approximately one teaspoon of cherry pie filling in the center of each square.Fold the squares diagonally to create little triangles and use a fork to crimp the edges of the triangle.'),
(2077, 331, 8, 'Carefully remove the skillet from your oven'),
(2078, 329, 10, 'Cut a tiny slice in the top of each triangle.  This lets the steam out during baking and also makes the turnovers look pretty because there will be a little cherry filling peeking through the top.'),
(2079, 331, 9, 'Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes, avocado and other toppings as desired'),
(2080, 334, 3, 'Add tomatoes, rice, 1/2 cup of cheese, broth and seasonings; mix well.'),
(2081, 329, 11, 'Place the turnovers on a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper or a Silpat.Repeat for the other section of dough.Chill the formed turnover cookies for about 10 minutes in the freezer to help them hold their shape during baking.Preheat oven to 350 F.'),
(2082, 328, 7, 'Place generous portions of slaw on the bottom buns, top with generous serving of BBQ jackfruit, and cashews.'),
