(2084, 329, 12, 'Remove cookie sheets from the freezer.'),
(2085, 334, 4, 'Transfer to a greased 13-in. x 9-in. baking dish. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.'),
(2086, 328, 8, 'Serve with extra BBQ sauce!Leftover jackfruit keeps for up to a couple days in the fridge, though best when fresh.'),
(2087, 329, 13, 'Bake for 20 minutes or until the turnover cookies are golden brown. It may take longer than 20 minutes if your turnover cookies are particularly cold. Although you can eat them before they brown (you won\'t get sick), they are so much better when they have time to get a little crispy. You don\'t want '),
(2088, 334, 5, 'Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.'),
(2089, 335, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line a cookie sheet with foil and top with a cookie rack sprayed with cooking spray.'),
(2090, 335, 2, 'Combine panko, pecans, thyme and salt on a plate.'),
(2091, 335, 3, 'Combine yogurt, water, lemon and lemon zest in a larger bowl.Dredge chicken tenders in yogurt and shake off excess. Press into panko and place on cookie rack.'),
(2092, 335, 4, 'Bake for 15 - 20 minutes until chicken is cooked through.If you\'d like a more browned tender, turn on the broiler for the last minute or two.'),
(2093, 336, 1, 'In large pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.'),
(2094, 336, 2, 'Add garlic, green pepper and onion; cook 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are softened, stirring occasionally.Stir in black pepper, salt and red pepper flakes; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in crushed tomatoes and broth; heat to boiling over medium-high heat.Stir in turkey and gnocchi; '),
(2095, 337, 1, 'In the bowl of a food processor, combine the olives and giardiniera. Pulse until pieces are approximately 1/4 inch in size.'),
(2096, 336, 3, 'Serve garnished with cheese.'),
(2097, 338, 1, 'first rinse and shred the cabbage and french beans. wipe the mushrooms with a wet cloth and then slice them. rinse, peel and grate the carrots. chop the onions, ginger and garlic.heat 1 tbsp oil in a pan or wok/kadai.add finely chopped onion, ginger and garlic. stir and saute on a medium flame for 2'),
(2098, 337, 2, 'Transfer the olive mixture to a bowl. Stir in the red wine vinegar and olive oil. Set aside. (Olive salad can be made up to 24 hours in advance.)'),
(2099, 339, 1, 'Cut mangos into small cubes. The easiest way to cut mangos is buy peeling it with a potato peeler and then cutting it into pieces. Put mango into a blender, with lemon juice.Blend until it is a smooth purée. Mango puree can stay refrigerated for several days in a fridge.'),
(2100, 342, 1, 'Spread walnuts evenly in small baking dish or pie pan, and bake at 350F until fragrant and lightly browned, stirring twice, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
(2101, 341, 1, 'For the cake, whisk together the egg whites, and 1/4 cup of the milk in small bowl until slightly combined. Set aside.In mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar for 2 minutes on medium.'),
(2102, 340, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),
(2103, 343, 1, 'Pour steel cut oats into pot of boiling water. Simmer for about 25 minutes.'),
(2104, 344, 1, 'Add all of the ingredients to the bowl of a food processor and process in short bursts until finely ground.   Chill for 1 hour before serving.'),
(2105, 345, 1, 'Butter a 9-inch deep-dish pie plate and dust with a tablespoon of sugar. Preheat the oven to 350F.Peel and slice the peaches. Toss with the raspberries. Set aside.Blend the sugar, milk, cream, eggs, vanilla, flour and salt in a blender for about a minute or until well blended.'),
(2106, 345, 2, 'Pour half the custard mixture into the prepared pie plate. Arrange fruit on top and pour the remaining custard over the fruit.'),
(2107, 337, 3, 'Split the bread in half lengthwise and spread the cut sides with the olive mixture.'),
(2108, 343, 2, 'Mix in apple pie spice, butter and brown sugar, stirring gently to combine.Spoon into individual serving bowls and top with portion of chopped apple'),
(2109, 340, 2, 'Place the chicken on a baking sheet and rub with the olive oil, chili powder, cumin, and paprika. Season with salt and pepper.'),
(2110, 341, 2, 'Add in dry ingredients and mix until combined. Slowly in a steady stream add in the egg white mixture. Beat in remaining milk and melted white chocolate bar.Fill cupcake liners half full with batter and bake in a 350 degree oven for about 15 minutes.'),
(2111, 339, 2, 'Place a few table spoons of mango puree, mint leaves and fill it with club soda. Optionally, you can add some ice to it.'),
(2112, 345, 3, 'Bake for 45-55 minutes, until the top is golden brown and puffy. Do not overcook. The custard should remain tender.'),
(2113, 337, 4, 'Layer the soppressata on the bottom half of the roll followed by the capicola, then salami, the mortadella and provolone. Arrange the arugula and the peppers on top of the provolone.'),
(2114, 340, 3, 'Add the poblano to the baking sheet.'),
(2115, 341, 3, 'Remove and cool in pan 5 minutes then transfer to a wire rack. Cool completely before frosting.For the frosting, beat butter 5 minutes until it becomes pale in color.'),
(2116, 345, 4, 'Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or creme anglaise.'),
(2117, 337, 5, 'Place the top of the roll on the sandwich and wrap tightly with plastic wrap.'),
(2118, 340, 4, 'Transfer to the oven and bake for 20 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through. Shred the chicken with two forks. De-seed the poblano and cut into slices.'),
