(2132, 346, 3, 'Remove onion and bay leaf.Turn off the heat and add 3/4 of the aged cheddar and all of the other cheeses. Season with salt and black pepper and fold in macaroni.'),
(2133, 346, 4, 'Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Top with remaining cheddar.Melt the remaining butter in a sauté pan and toss bread crumbs and parsley to coat. Top the macaroni with bread crumb mixture.'),
(2134, 346, 5, 'Bake for 30 minutes.'),
(2135, 346, 6, 'Remove from the oven let stand for about 5 minutes.'),
(2136, 346, 7, 'Serve with fresh shaved black truffles.'),
(2137, 347, 1, 'In a large bowl, toss together salad ingredients.In a small bowl, whisk together cherry juice, balsamic vinegar, dijon and grainy mustard, garlic, and honey.Slowly whisk in the olive oil until throughly combined. '),
(2138, 348, 1, 'Wet a piece of cheesecloth large enough to line the sieve or colander with a double layer and squeeze out the excess water.  Line the sieve or colander and set over a large bowl.  Set aside.Put milk, heavy cream, and salt in a large, heavy bottomed stock pot and bring to a rolling boil over medium h'),
(2139, 349, 1, 'Mix all the ingredients except oil with a fork until smooth.'),
(2140, 350, 1, 'Melt butter with mint leaves over medium heat in a small skillet or heavy-bottomed pot.Continue to heat the butter, stirring periodically, until it turns brown (10-15 minutes). The butter will first boil with big bubbles (it\'s not done then). Then, the bubbles will get smaller and the whole thing wi'),
(2141, 352, 1, 'Preheat your oven to 400 degrees.In a saucepan on the stove, over low heat, melt the butter and saute the garlic for 1-2 minutes.'),
(2142, 353, 1, 'In a medium stainless steel saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Sweat onion until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes.'),
(2143, 354, 1, 'To create the batter, mix all ingredients, except fish, in a wide-bottomed bowl. The batter should be a consistency just slightly thicker than pancake batter.'),
(2144, 355, 1, 'Light a grill over medium heat. In a medium bowl, combine ground turkey, red onions, jalapeos and Worcestershire sauce.'),
(2145, 347, 2, 'Add salt and pepper to taste.Toss the salad with as little or as much dressing as you like right before serving.');
INSERT INTO `instruction` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `step_num`, `instruction`) VALUES
(2146, 348, 2, 'Pour the mixture into the lined sieve or colander and let it drain for an hour. Gently squeeze any excess whey out of the ricotta, store in an airtight container, and chill.'),
(2147, 349, 2, 'Heat a non stick pan and pour ½ tbsp oil in it. When the oil is very hot pour a ladle of batter on the same point in the pan and roll the panfrom side to side to give the batter a round shape.Cook it for 1 or 2 minutes. Just check the bottom with a wooden spatula when it releases and flip when it ha'),
(2148, 350, 2, 'Remove butter from heat and strain the mint leaves out.  Press the butter out of the them as best you can.  Don\'t worry if you don\'t get it all - it\'s impossible  You only need 1/2 cup of the mint-flavored butter in the cookies.Cool the butter to room temperature - about thirty minutes.Preheat oven '),
(2149, 352, 2, 'Add the tomato sauce.'),
(2150, 353, 2, 'Add garlic and pepper, and cook for about 1 minute.'),
(2151, 354, 2, 'Heat 2 Tbsp of oil in a large, non-stick frying pan until the oil pops when water is sprinkled on it.Dip your fish fillets into the batter, coating well on both sides. Gently lay fish in the hot oil (carefully, because it will splatter). Repeat with remaining fillets to fill the pan with just enough'),
(2152, 355, 2, 'Mix thoroughly. Divide the mixture into four equal portions. Form four patties with hands and place on the lighted grill. Cook for 5 minutes on each side or until desired level of done-ness is reached.'),
(2153, 349, 3, 'Serve these right after you make with various fillings aside.'),
(2154, 350, 3, 'Mix in egg white and white chocolate.In a separate bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.'),
(2155, 352, 3, 'Heat to boiling, then remove from heat.Stir to combine everything as much as possible.Rinse chicken and then pat dry with towel.'),
(2156, 353, 3, 'Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, and water; stir to combine. Reduce heat to medium-low and let simmer for approximately 15 minutes or until thickened slightly, stirring occasionally.'),
(2157, 354, 3, 'Remove fish from pan to a plate lined with paper towels to soak up extra grease.Preheat oven to 450F.'),
(2158, 350, 4, 'Add flour mixture to butter mixture a little bit at a time until just combined.'),
(2159, 352, 4, 'Place chicken in a square glass baking dish. Cover with the sauce and bake in oven at 400 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.While chicken is cooking, cook rice, pasta or quinoa and maybe grill up some veggies for a side dish.When chicken is done serve chicken and sauce over pasta, rice or quinoa.We toppe'),
(2160, 353, 4, 'Remove soup from heat.'),
(2161, 354, 4, 'Place cut potatoes in a large bowl, spray lightly with cooking spray and toss to coat.Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Grease the foil with cooking spray and place potatoes on foil. Sprinkle with salt or seasoned salt to taste.'),
(2162, 350, 5, 'Place teaspoon-sized balls of dough about 1 1/2 inches apart on a parchment- or Silpat-lined cookie sheet.  The dough will be a little crumbly, so just push it together with your hands if you need to.'),
(2163, 353, 5, 'Add the yogurt, the soup, cumin and salt to a blender. Blend until soup is smooth (To avoid spillage, make sure to press the lid of the blender on tightly).'),
(2164, 354, 5, 'Bake potatoes for 15 min.'),
(2165, 350, 6, 'Bake for 7-9 minutes or until the edges begin to brown.'),
(2166, 353, 6, 'Pour in glass shots or bowls, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, and garnish with cilantro or parsley if desired. Spicy tomato soup can be accompanied by mini grilled cheese sandwiches. This recipe yields 5 (8-ounce) cups of soup.NOTE: To make Mini Grilled Cheese Sandwiches, sprinkle Kraft Grated Parm'),
(2167, 354, 6, 'Remove from oven and turn the chips with a spatula. Return to oven to bake an additional 10 – 15 min. Chips are done when crisp and golden.'),
(2168, 350, 7, 'Transfer to a cooling rack to cool.'),
(2169, 356, 1, 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
(2170, 356, 2, 'In a large bowl, toss the apples with the sugar, lemon zest and juice, rum (if using), vanilla, cornstarch, nutmeg and salt. Macerate at room temperature for about 2 hours or, refrigerated, overnight.'),
(2171, 356, 3, 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),
(2172, 356, 4, 'Dust a worktop and rolling pin with flour.'),
(2173, 356, 5, 'Roll out one dough disk a little less than 1/4-inch thick, about 14 inches in diameter. Fold the dough in half and transfer it to a 9- or 10-inch pie plate. Unfold. Press the dough into the corners, leaving the overhang. Refrigerate the first crust while you roll out the second disk of dough.'),
(2174, 356, 6, 'Remove the bottom crust from the fridge and fill it with the macerated apples. Tuck the pats of cold butter beneath the top layer of fruit. Top with the second piece of dough, and trim both to a 1/2-inch overhang. Tuck the overhang into a roll and crimp the edge, pressing down to hook some of the do'),
(2175, 356, 7, 'Cut a hole in the center of the pie, as well as some decorative vents.'),
(2176, 356, 8, 'Brush the top of the pie with cream, dust it with sugar, and bake for 20 minutes.'),
(2177, 356, 9, 'Then reduce the temperature to 350 degrees F and bake for another 45 to 55 minutes, until the center juices bubble and thicken, for a total of about 1 hour 10 minutes.'),
(2178, 356, 10, 'Let the pie cool until it is just warm to the touch before slicing and serving.'),
(2179, 356, 11, 'Mix the flour, sugar, and salt in a large bowl.'),
(2180, 356, 12, 'Add the lard and the butter, and cut them in with a pastry blender until the larger pieces are the size of peas and the mixture begins to clump on the pastry blender. Shuffle through the mixture with your hands, pinching chunks of lard to flatten them.'),
(2181, 356, 13, 'Add 4 tablespoons of the ice water and mix with a fork. Pinch a clump of dough in your hands: If it feels moist and clumps together easily, it\'s probably hydrated enough. If it feels really crumbly, add another tablespoon or two of ice water until you can form a baseball-size clump of dough, packing'),
(2182, 356, 14, 'Divide the dough in half and form each half into a flat disk. Wrap both disks in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour and up to 2 days.'),
(2183, 356, 15, 'Thirty minutes before you\'re ready to roll out the dough, remove it from the refrigerator and let it sit at room temperature to soften.'),
(2184, 357, 1, 'First up, prep your kale by washing it well and cutting it off of the stem.The massage the kale leaves in a large bowl with a drizzle of olive oil, half of the lemon juice and a pinch of kosher salt. This is the secret to tasty raw kale! The prep the red onions and red pepper.Meanwhile, make the dre'),
(2185, 357, 2, 'Whisk together tahini, extra virgin olive oil, vinegar, water, lemon juice, smoked paprika, and salt and pepper to taste.Now add the red onions and red peppers to the kale and dress with the tahini dressing and sesame seeds.Toss and garnish with avocado, goat cheese and sunflower seeds.'),
(2186, 358, 1, 'For the cookies:In a mixing bowl whisk together flour and salt. In the bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream together butter and sugar until well combined (scrape bowl occasionally throughout entire mixing process).'),
(2187, 359, 1, 'To make sauce: In a small saucepan, combine the raspberries, sugar and lemon juice. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat, mashing the berries with a spoon.'),
(2188, 360, 1, 'Cook the pasta according to package directions.'),
(2189, 361, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees (F). Cook pasta according to package directions. Do not overcook!'),
(2190, 359, 2, 'Remove from heat and press through a fine-mesh sieve using the back of a spoon. Collect sauce in a bowl. Refrigerate until cold.For mousse: In a microwave safe bowl, combine white chocolate and  cup heavy cream. Microwave in 30 seconds intervals, stirring in between until chocolate is melted.In a la'),
(2191, 358, 2, 'Mix in egg yolks and vanilla extract then with mixer set on low speed, slowly add in flour mixture and mix just until combined. Scoop dough out 1 Tbsp at a time (24g) and shape into balls then place on a flat surface and make an indentation in middle of cookies with thumb.'),
(2192, 360, 2, 'Drain and reserve 1/4 cup of cooking liquid.'),
(2193, 361, 2, 'Drain and set aside.Salt and pepper both sides of the pieces of chicken. Dredge chicken in flour.'),
