(3219, 526, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees and line a baking sheet with a silpat or parchment paper. If you don\'t have either, spray lightly with cooking spray to avoid sticking.In a blender, preferably a twister jar from Blendtec, blend the almonds to create a thick almond butter. If it gets too hot, set asid'),
(3220, 526, 2, 'Add  Cup almond butter to a large bowl along with the bananas, maple syrup, molasses, orange zest, and spices.'),
(3221, 528, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 325 F. Line an 8 x 8-inch baking pan with parchment paper. In a small bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, and sugar. Toss with a fork until evenly mixed.'),
(3222, 526, 3, 'Mix, mashing the bananas as you stir so that they are well incorporated but small chunks remain.'),
(3223, 529, 1, 'In a large skillet, combine carrot, ham, pineapple, pineapple juice*, soy sauce, worcestershire sauce, broth, and salt and bring to a boil over medium high heat.Stir in rice and cover.'),
(3224, 527, 1, 'Combine the flour, sugar, and salt in a bowl.'),
(3225, 527, 2, 'Add the cubed butter and toss to coat. Dump the mixture out onto a clean surface and use a rolling pin to roll the butter into thin sheets, combining it with the flour. Use a bench scraper to scrape the rolling pin and to bring the mixture back into a pile as necessary. Continue until all of the but'),
(3226, 528, 2, 'Transfer the mixture to the prepared pan and press into an even layer in the bottom of the pan. Sprinkle the toffee bits in an even layer over the graham cracker mixture.'),
(3227, 528, 3, 'Bake for 5 minutes.'),
(3228, 528, 4, 'Remove the pan from the oven, but maintain the oven temperature.To make the filling, in the bowl of an electric mixer, combine the cream cheese and sour cream. Beat on medium-high speed until smooth and well combined, 1-2 minutes. Beat in the sugar. Blend in the egg, vanilla, and salt, scraping down'),
(3229, 527, 3, 'Mixture will be very flaky. Return mixture to the bowl and place in the freezer for 15 minutes to chill the butter.'),
(3230, 526, 4, 'Add the oats, chocolate chips and craisins and fold everything together.Using a cookie dough scoop or two spoons, scoop the dough into balls on the cookie sheet. Press the tops gently to flatten them out as these will not spread at all.'),
(3231, 529, 2, 'Remove from heat and let sit for 5 minutes until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Stir in green onions and serve.'),
(3232, 527, 4, 'Remove from freezer and add the buttermilk. Use a spoon and then your hands to stir the mixture until it comes together into a ball. If mixture is too dry, add the water a tablespoon at a time. Divide the dough in two and flatten into disks. Wrap each disk in plastic wrap and chill in the fridge for'),
(3233, 528, 5, 'Pour the mixture over the crust in an even layer.Return the pan to the oven and bake just until set, about 30-35 minutes.'),
(3234, 526, 5, 'Bake at 350 for 10 minutes and serve warm or place in a sealed container and store in the fridge for up to 1 week.');
INSERT INTO `instruction` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `step_num`, `instruction`) VALUES
(3235, 528, 6, 'Transfer the pan to a wire cooling rack and let cool to room temperature. Cover with foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours.'),
(3236, 527, 5, 'While the dough is chilling, make the peach pie filling. In a large bowl, combine peaches, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cornstarch, and vanilla extract. Gently stir until mixed well.'),
(3237, 528, 7, 'Drizzle additional caramel sauce over the cheesecake and sprinkle with additional toffee bits. Slice into squares with a large kitchen knife. Refrigerate until ready to serve.'),
(3238, 527, 6, 'When ready to roll out, let the dough rest at room temperature for five minutes. On a lightly floured surface, use a rolling pin to roll out the dough into a rough 13 inch circle. Dough should be about 1/4 inch thick.'),
(3239, 527, 7, 'Transfer dough to pie dish. Fill pie with peach filling. Repeat with the second disk of dough.'),
(3240, 527, 8, 'Cut dough and make a lattice over the filling. You can also leave the circle intact and cover the filling completely, cutting a few vents with a sharp knife, but I went with a lattice top for my peach pie.'),
(3241, 527, 9, 'Fold the edges of the top and bottom crusts together and use your index fingers and thumb to pinch into a pattern.'),
(3242, 527, 10, 'Brush with egg wash and sprinkle with turbinado sugar.'),
(3243, 527, 11, 'Bake in a 400 degrees F oven for 45 minutes or until the pie is bubbling and the crust is golden brown.'),
(3244, 527, 12, 'Let the pie cool completely on a wire cooling rack before cutting. Note-you can use this same pie crust to make apple pie, berry pie, strawberry rhubarb pie, etc. Use your favorite filling!'),
(3245, 530, 1, 'Blend all ingredients except ice in a blender (I use a Blendtec). Blend well on high speed, at least a minute, up to 2 minutes depending on blender. Push through a fine mesh strainer to remove pulp.'),
(3246, 530, 2, 'Serve with ice.'),
(3247, 532, 1, 'Sift together the dry ingredients (flour through salt).  I just scraped mine through a fine strainer/sieve since my sifter isn\'t all that great.  Set aside.'),
(3248, 532, 2, 'Use an electric mixer to combine the butter and sugars- mixing until the mixture is very light, about 5 minutes.'),
(3249, 532, 3, 'Mix in the eggs, one at a time.'),
(3250, 531, 1, 'Pour tequila, simple syrup and grapefruit juice in champagne glass and stir gently to combine.'),
(3251, 532, 4, 'Add the vanilla.  Reduce the speed to low, add the dry ingredients and, mix just until the dry ingredients are incorporated.  Stir in the chocolate chips.'),
(3252, 533, 1, 'Bring large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.Meanwhile, in large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.'),
(3253, 532, 5, 'Place the dough in an airtight container and refrigerate a minimum of 24 to 36 hours before baking (and up to 72 hours).'),
(3254, 531, 2, 'Add chilled sparkling wine and serve immediately.'),
(3255, 533, 2, 'Add onion and fennel and cook, stirring often, until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
(3256, 532, 6, 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.  Line baking sheets with parchment paper or silpat mats.'),
(3257, 533, 3, 'Add garlic and fennel seeds and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Stir in broth and lima beans and bring to a simmer. Stir in green beans and salt, reduce heat to medium and simmer until all beans are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
(3258, 533, 4, 'Add tomatoes and olives and simmer, stirring occasionally, until flavors have blended, about 5 minutes. Stir in parsley and pepper.Shortly before sauce is ready, add bow ties to boiling water; stir to prevent sticking. Cook, stirring often, until just tender, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
(3259, 533, 5, 'Drain well and place in large warm serving bowl.'),
(3260, 533, 6, 'Add bean mixture and toss to coat.'),
(3261, 532, 7, 'For 5-inch cookies, scoop six 3.25 ounce mounds of dough- giant golf ball-sized (I rolled mine into balls) onto a baking sheet, spacing them evenly apart.  Don\'t try to fit more on the sheet or you\'ll end up with cookies baking into each other.  Dot some extra chocolate chips on top, if desired.  Sp'),
(3262, 535, 1, 'Preheat oven to 350°F. Butter 8- or 9-inch square cake pan.'),
(3263, 532, 8, 'Bake until the edges are golden brown and the center is lighter and soft, 18 to 20 minutes.'),
(3264, 533, 7, 'Serve sprinkled with Parmesan if desired.'),
(3265, 534, 1, 'I used my 6-Quart slow cooker.'),
(3266, 532, 9, 'Let the cookies cool on the baking sheet for about 15 minutes, then transfer the cookies to a rack and let them cool completely.  Repeat with the remaining cookie dough.'),
(3267, 535, 2, 'Stir together flour, sweetener and baking powder in bowl. Beat together butter, eggs and vanilla in separate bowl until butter is broken into little pieces.'),
(3268, 536, 1, 'to make the milk crumb:Preheat oven to 250°F.  Line large rimmed baking sheet with parchment.'),
(3269, 535, 3, 'Add applesauce, and stir until blended. Fold in flour mixture until moistened. Fold in white chocolate. Measure out 1/2 cup of mixture, and drop by spoonfuls into prepared pan.'),
(3270, 535, 4, 'Fold cocoa powder and chocolate chips into remaining batter. Gently spoon chocolate batter over white batter. Batter is thick, so smooth out surface.'),
(3271, 536, 2, 'Combine 1/2 cup milk powder, flour, sugar, cornstarch, and coarse salt in medium bowl; toss to mix evenly.'),
(3272, 534, 2, 'Add the vegetables, salt, bay leaves, thyme, pepper and water to your slow cooker.Cover and cook on LOW for 6 to 8 hours or until the vegetables are very tender.Turn your slow cooker to warm.With an immersion blender, carefully puree the soup to the desired consistency, as coarse or smooth as you li'),
(3273, 535, 5, 'Bake 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool before cutting into 1 1/2-inch squares.'),
(3274, 536, 3, 'Add butter and stir until clusters form.'),
(3275, 536, 4, 'Spread mixture evenly on prepared sheet.'),
(3276, 536, 5, 'Bake until crumbs are dry and crumbly but still pale, about 20 minutes.  Cool completely.  Crumble any large clusters, and transfer all of the crumbs to a bowl.'),
(3277, 536, 6, 'Add the additional 1/4 cup milk powder and toss.'),
(3278, 537, 1, 'Place all ingredients in a food processor or blender and puree until smooth.'),
(3279, 537, 2, 'Add water to thin if needed.'),
(3280, 537, 3, 'Serve over green salad or use as a dip for veggies.'),
(3281, 538, 1, 'In a medium sauce pan melt 3 TBSP of the butter over medium heat.'),
(3282, 538, 2, 'Add the onion and garlic and cook until translucent.'),
(3283, 538, 3, 'Add in the water and milk and bring to a simmer. While whisking continuously, slowly pour in the cornmeal. Continue whisking until the mixture starts to thicken. Heavily season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
(3284, 538, 4, 'Mix in the thyme, asiago cheese, and the rest of the butter (2 TBSP).'),
(3285, 538, 5, 'Add more warm milk as needed if the mixture starts becoming too thick.'),
(3286, 538, 6, 'Serve warm topped with more asiago cheese, a poached egg, and crumbled bacon. Makes 4 servings.'),
(3287, 539, 1, 'Gently whisk together all ingredients.'),
(3288, 539, 2, 'Let rest on the counter for 5 minutes.Lightly grease a griddle and turn heat to medium.'),
(3289, 540, 1, 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
(3290, 539, 3, 'Pour batter onto the griddle 1/4 cup at a time (the amount is important for these-- they will crack if you make them bigger than 1/4 cup) and cook on one side until bubbles form on the top and do not fill back in. Flip and cook for another minute or two on the other side.'),
(3291, 540, 2, 'Special equipment: an 8-inch nonstick skillet'),
(3292, 541, 1, 'In a small bowl, combine the lemon juice, oil, parsley, pepper and salt. Thread the broccoli, onion, salmon, garlic cloves and squash onto 24 small wooden skewers; spoon lemon juice mixture over kabobs.'),
(3293, 540, 3, 'Set a large strainer or colander over a bowl and line it with a clean kitchen towel. Using a box grater, grate the potatoes and onion into the strainer. Using the towel, squeeze as much liquid from the potatoes and onion as possible.'),
(3294, 540, 4, 'Transfer the mixture to another bowl and stir in the flour, eggs, chives, baking powder, salt and pepper.'),
(3295, 540, 5, 'Coat the bottom of an 8-inch nonstick skillet with oil and add a couple of tablespoons of butter.'),
(3296, 540, 6, 'Heat over medium heat until the butter foam subsides. Spoon about 1 3/4 cups of the potato mixture into the pan and press to fill the circumference. Fry over medium heat, flipping once, until the pancake is golden and crisp, 3 to 4 minutes per side.'),
(3297, 540, 7, 'Drain the pancake on a paper towel-lined baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining batter.'),
(3298, 541, 2, 'Place skewers in a steamer basket; place in a large saucepan over 1 in. of water. Bring to a boil; cover and steam for 12-15 minutes or until salmon flakes easily with a fork and vegetables are crisp-tender.'),
(3299, 542, 1, 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),
(3300, 542, 2, 'To make the souffle base, mix together the flour, butter, milk, egg yolks, Stilton, mustard, salt, and pepper, and mix until smooth and set aside. This maybe be prepared a day ahead of time.'),
(3301, 542, 3, 'In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites, corn flour, and salt until stiff but fluffy.'),
(3303, 542, 4, 'Add a small amount of the egg whites to the souffle base and blend.'),
(3304, 544, 1, 'To Caramelize Onion:: Preheat a skillet over medium-high heat.'),
(3305, 545, 1, 'In a small bowl, combine the mustard, mayonnaise, onion powder, dill, salt and pepper.'),
(3306, 545, 2, 'Combine the chopped eggs and dressing.'),
(3307, 544, 2, 'Add in butter and allow to melt and start to simmer.'),
(3308, 547, 1, 'Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan set over medium heat.'),
(3309, 542, 5, 'Add the remaining egg whites to the mixture and fold gently. Gently spoon in the mixture into 6 buttered ramekins and place in the oven.'),
(3310, 548, 1, 'Preheat a medium heavy griddle or cast-iron pan over medium-high heat.'),
(3312, 545, 3, 'Place in the fridge to chill for a couple of minutes.'),
(3313, 544, 3, 'Add in thinly sliced onion and toss to coat in butter.'),
(3314, 544, 4, 'Let simmer and stir occassionally until the onions turn golden brown and reduce down.'),
(3315, 545, 4, 'Place some egg salad on each tortilla and a couple leaves of spinach. Enjoy!!!'),
(3317, 548, 2, 'Add the whole tomatoes, serrano chile and shallot and roast on the dry skillet, turning frequently, until golden brown on all sides, about 8 minutes.'),
(3318, 546, 1, 'Line a baking sheet or counter top with parchment paper. In a small bowl, microwave dark chocolate in 30 second intervals, stirring each time, until smooth.Dip half (or whole!) marshmallow in melted dark chocolate and immediately sandwich between two original Pretzel Crisps. Eat immediately for a me'),
(3319, 547, 2, 'Add the onions and cook until they are tender, about 5 minutes.To the onions, add the rice, garlic, vinegar and rosemary.  Stir, cooking, until the rice is coated, about 1 minute.Stir in the beets, kale and vegetable broth.Bring the mixture to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to medium-low.Cook un'),
(3320, 542, 6, 'Bake souffles for approximately 10 minutes until they have risen and are golden. Once you remove them from the oven, allow to rest for 1 minute before serving.'),
(3321, 544, 5, 'Remove from skillet and add to sandwich.For Paninis::Preheat Panini Maker to 375 degrees. If you don\'t have a panini press - make this like a grilled cheese, it\'s fantastic!Top slices of bread with mayonnaise and dijon mustard. Top slice of bread with turkey, tomato, caramelized onion, spinach and t'),
(3323, 548, 3, 'Transfer the vegetables and chile to a food processor and add the chicken broth and cilantro. Pulse until smooth but with some small pieces remaining, or to the desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper.'),
(3324, 549, 1, 'Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease two 9-inch round cake pans, line bottoms with parchment, grease parchment, and flour. (**I used two 6-inch round cake pans, although there is enough batter for three 6-inch cake pans if desired. You can follow Wilton\'s guidelin'),
(3325, 547, 3, 'Serve, grating 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese over each serving.'),
(3326, 542, 7, 'To prepare the salad, mix all of the ingredients together.'),
(3327, 544, 6, 'Remove from press, slice and serve.'),
(3329, 548, 4, 'Serve immediately or cool to room temperature and store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 5 days.'),
(3330, 549, 2, 'Transfer strawberries to bowl, cover, and microwave until strawberries are soft and have released their juice, about 5-7 minutes, stirring once halfway through.'),
(3331, 549, 3, 'Place strawberries in a fine-mesh strainer set over small saucepan. Firmly press fruit dry (juice should measure at least 3/4 cup); discard strawberry solids. Bring juice to boil over medium-high heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until syrupy and reduced to 1/4 cup, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
(3332, 542, 8, 'To serve, place the salad on each plate on the side and remove the souffle from the ramekins and invert 1 onto each plate. Top the souffle with chopped walnuts.'),
(3333, 550, 1, 'Place all green layer ingredients in the blender and blend until smooth.'),
(3334, 549, 4, 'Whisk together strawberry juice, milk, egg whites, and vanilla in bowl, and set aside. Using a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt on low speed until combined.'),
(3335, 550, 2, 'Pour into serving glasses.Rinse blender jar.'),
(3336, 550, 3, 'Place red layer ingredients in the blender and blend until smooth.Using a spoon, add the red layer over the green layer in your smoothie glasses. I spooned the strawberry layer close to the edge of the glass and pushed it down with a straw, to create the lava effect.'),
(3337, 549, 5, 'Add butter, 1 piece at a time, and mix until only pea-size pieces remain, about 1 minute.'),
(3338, 550, 4, 'Serve immediately.'),
(3339, 549, 6, 'Add half of strawberry mixture, increase speed to medium-high, and beat until light and fluffy, about 1 minute. Reduce speed to medium-low, add remaining milk mixture, and beat until incorporated, about 30 seconds. Give batter final stir by hand, being sure to mix in any clumps on the bottom of the '),
(3340, 549, 7, 'Remove cakes from pans, discarding parchment, and cool completely, about 2 hours.Use a knife or a cake leveler to level out the cakes so that they are perfectly flat. Then add a thick and even layer of frosting on top of the first cake, and set the second cake on top. Continue to frost the entire ca'),
(3341, 549, 8, 'Serve immediately, or store in a covered container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, mix the cream cheese and butter on medium speed until smooth.'),
(3342, 549, 9, 'Add the sugar and vanilla and mix at low speed until combined. If you need to thicken the frosting, add more powdered sugar. If you need to thin, add a teaspoon or two of milk.**For easier slicing, I recommend placing the hearts in vertical rows instead of alternately spaced. You also totally don\'t '),
(3343, 551, 1, 'Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Once oil is shimmering, add the onions, garlic, celery and red pepper flakes. Cook until celery is soft.'),
(3344, 551, 2, 'Add the vegetable broth and water and bring to a simmer. Once simmering, add the kale, quinoa, carrot noodles, thyme, rosemary, and season with salt and pepper, and let cook until carrot noodles are softened, 3-5 minutes. Stir in the Parmesan and serve.'),
(3345, 552, 1, 'Mince the cilantro leaves and place in a bowl. Using a microplane, grate the garlic on to the cilantro, followed by the lime zest. Toss together and set side.'),
(3346, 552, 2, 'Heat olive oil over medium heat in skillet.'),
(3347, 554, 1, 'In a small bowl, combine rum, coconut milk, pineapple juice, and vanilla. Set aside.    In a medium-sized bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.    In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.'),
(3348, 553, 1, 'Add the shredded potatoes to a bowl of water, stir to combine.'),
(3349, 553, 2, 'Pour the potatoes over a wire mesh strainer and allow to drain.'),
(3350, 555, 1, 'In a large bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.  Make a well in the dry ingredients, and add the wet into the dry; mix until just combined.'),
(3351, 554, 2, 'Add eggs to the sugar mixture one at a time, beating well after each addition.    Alternately add the flour mixture and the rum mixture, beating well after each addition.    Fold in the coconut and pineapple.    Fill cupcake liners 3/4 full.'),
(3352, 552, 3, 'Add onions and let cook until onions begin to soften, 3-4 minutes. Next, stir in sweet potatoes and continue to cook for another 3-4 minutes.In a mortar and pestle, combine the chipotle, adobo sauce, honey, and lime juice. Break apart the chipotle into small pieces (alternatively, you can cut up the'),
(3353, 556, 1, 'Put a large pot of water on to boil. Fill another large pot half full with ice water. Blanch about half the green beans in the boiling water just until tender, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
(3354, 554, 3, 'Bake at 350 F for 25 minutes or until cupcakes bounce back when lightly touched.'),
(3355, 552, 4, 'Pour into the pan with the sweet potatoes and reduce the heat to medium-low.Cook until sweet potatoes have softened, 10-15 minutes.'),
(3356, 555, 2, 'Heat a large skillet over medium-low heat. Grease skilled with butter or nonstick cooking spray.'),
(3357, 553, 3, 'Whisk the egg and egg white in a large glass mixing bowl until just incorporated, about 30 seconds. Sift the flour, granulated garlic, cayenne and cinnamon into the egg.'),
(3358, 557, 1, 'Combine dressing, 2 Tbsp. hot sauce and celery.'),
(3359, 556, 2, 'Remove with a slotted spoon and plunge into the ice water.'),
(3360, 554, 4, 'Mix cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy.'),
(3361, 552, 5, 'Let cool.Preheat oven to 35'),
(3362, 555, 3, 'Add 1/4 cup batter per pancake. Cook until bubbles form and the edges start to look dry, about 2 minutes.  Flip pancake over, and cook for 1-2 minutes, or until the other side is lightly browned.  Meanwhile, make the caramelized bananas. Melt the butter in a separate skillet over medium-low heat.'),
(3363, 553, 4, 'Add the chives. Sprinkle with 3 teaspoons each salt and black pepper; whisk until smooth. Fold in the sweet potato and potato, making sure the batter is thoroughly combined.'),
(3364, 557, 2, 'Cook chicken in butter in small skillet on medium heat 3 min. or until heated through, stirring frequently.  Stir in remaining hot sauce.'),
(3365, 556, 3, 'Transfer to a large bowl. Repeat with the remaining beans.Return the water to a boil.'),
(3366, 554, 5, 'Mix in powdered sugar a little bit at a time.'),
(3367, 552, 6, 'Brush the corn tortillas with olive oil and cut into strips.'),
(3368, 555, 4, 'Add the butter and let it melt. Once the most of the butter has melted, stir in the sugar; continue stirring until the sugar melts.'),
(3369, 553, 5, 'Set a large cast-iron or heavy-bottomed skillet over medium heat.'),
(3370, 557, 3, 'Fill buns with cheese, chicken mixture and dressing mixture.'),
(3371, 556, 4, 'Add corn and blanch until tender but still crisp, about 3 minutes.'),
(3372, 554, 6, 'Mix in coconut cream.    Pipe or spread on cupcakes.'),
(3373, 552, 7, 'Spread in a single layer on a sheet tray.'),
(3374, 555, 5, 'Add the banana slices, and cook until the bananas begin to soften and caramelize.  Flip bananas over and continue cooking until the other side has caramelized, about 2-3 minutes.'),
(3375, 553, 6, 'Add the oil. Working in small batches, drop about 3 tablespoons per latke into the skillet just before the oil begins to smoke. Flatten each slightly with a slotted metal spatula. Make sure to not overcrowd the skillet.'),
(3376, 556, 5, 'Drain and immediately plunge into the ice water.'),
(3377, 552, 8, 'Bake until brown and golden, roughly 10 minutes.Assemble the salad with lettuce, gremolata, black beans, pepitas, cheese, sweet potatoes, and crispy tortillas.'),
(3378, 552, 9, 'Whisk together the olive oil and lime juice, pour over the salad, and toss until well combined.'),
(3379, 553, 7, 'Crisp the latkes until the bottoms are caramelized, 2 to 3 minutes. Flip with the spatula and continue crisping the second side for about 6 minutes total. The latkes should be cooked through and a dark, golden brown.'),
(3380, 555, 6, 'Add the pecans, if using, and stir to combine.'),
(3381, 553, 8, 'Transfer to a paper-towel-lined dish. Season lightly with salt and pepper.'),
(3382, 555, 7, 'Pour the banana sauce over hot pancakes.'),
(3383, 553, 9, 'Serve immediately, garnishing each latke center with a small dollop of sour cream and a sprinkle of torn parsley leaves.'),
(3384, 556, 6, 'Cut the kernels off the cobs.'),
(3385, 556, 7, 'Add the corn to the beans in the bowl.'),
(3386, 556, 8, 'Add bell pepper, onion, olives, basil, oil, vinegar, lemon juice and garlic; toss to mix well. Season with hot sauce, salt and pepper.'),
(3387, 558, 1, 'Make the flatbread'),
(3388, 559, 1, 'In a large frying pan over medium heat, cook the meat until almost browned. A little pink is okay as it\'ll be simmering for a while later on.'),
(3389, 558, 2, 'Mix together the water and honey in a small bowl.'),
(3390, 558, 3, 'Place the flours, sugar, and salt in the bowl of a food processor fitted with the steel blade. Pulse a few times to combine well. Turn on the processor and slowly stream in the water mixture. This should take about 30 seconds. Continue to mix for 1 1/2 minutes, until the dough comes together. It sho'),
(3391, 559, 2, 'Add the rest of the ingredients to the pan, except for the cheddar cheese, and stir together. Cover with a lid and simmer for 20 - 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. This is using whole wheat pasta. It might take less time if you use the regular stuff. If you find that too much of the liquid has eva'),
(3392, 560, 1, 'Put all the ingredients in a bowl and mix together.  I used a fork to mash the avocado up.  You could also use a food processor or small blender if you prefer.'),
(3393, 558, 4, 'Set up a pasta roller on your work surface. Using a rolling pin, pound the dough into a 1-inch-thick rectangle, the width of your pasta roller. Dust with all-purpose flour as necessary.'),
(3394, 558, 5, 'Roll out the dough, cutting it into pieces to make it easier to handle as you move through increasingly narrow settings, until it is 1/8 inch thick. Lightly dust with flour each time you roll it through.'),
(3395, 558, 6, 'Place on lightly dusted pieces of parchment paper, stack the parchment, wrap in plastic, and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or overnight.'),
(3396, 558, 7, 'Place a rack in the lowest position of the oven and preheat the oven to 450°F (230°C) with a pizza stone in it.Top and bake the flatbread'),
(3397, 558, 8, 'Working with one sheet at a time, lay the dough out on your lightly dusted work surface.'),
(3398, 558, 9, 'Brush evenly with a light coating of olive oil and sprinkle on a light coating of shallots.'),
(3399, 558, 10, 'Mix together the salt, Parmesan, and thyme and sprinkle over the dough.'),
(3400, 558, 11, 'Cut the sheet crosswise on the diagonal to make 18 triangles, 3 inches across at the bottom.'),
(3401, 558, 12, 'Place 4 or 5 triangles at a time on the hot baking stone and bake for 5 to 7 minutes, until blistered and browned.'),
(3402, 558, 13, 'Remove from the stone and allow to cool on a rack before serving.'),
(3403, 561, 1, 'In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, butter and egg. Press into the bottom of a 13x9 baking dish.'),
(3404, 561, 2, 'Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla eggs in a mixer. Beat until fluffy.'),
(3405, 561, 3, 'Pour over crust.'),
(3406, 561, 4, 'Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30-35 minutes.'),
(3407, 561, 5, 'Remove from oven and cool completely. Refrigerate for 4 hours (or overnight) for best flavor. ENJOY.'),
(3408, 562, 1, 'Heat olive oil in a large soup pot over medium heat.'),
(3409, 565, 1, 'First cook, cool and peel your eggs.'),
(3410, 563, 1, '1'),
(3411, 565, 2, 'Cut them in half and gently remove the yolks, placing them in a medium bowl.'),
(3412, 567, 1, 'Using a food processor, reduce the Oreo cookies to crumbs.'),
(3413, 563, 2, 'In a medium bowl soak the mushrooms in cold water until soften about 30 minutes.  Thinly slice the mushrooms and set aside.'),
(3414, 562, 2, 'Add onion and saut until they start to soften, about 3 minutes.'),
